claim: Vaccination with a higher-dose recombinant flu vaccine may induce a more robust antibody response than egg-based standard-dose vaccines.
explanation: A table comparing demographic and clinical characteristics of adults aged 18–64 and ≥65 years by vaccine received (recombinant quadrivalent influenza vaccine [RIV4] versus standard-dose egg-based quadrivalent influenza vaccine [SD-IIV4], and in ≥65 also high-dose and adjuvanted egg-based vaccines). Variables include race, sex, season, influenza cases, and high-risk conditions with counts, percentages, and P-values. does not support the claim because the table only presents demographic and case-status comparisons, not any measures of antibody response or immunogenicity.
